The Uganda senior women’s national cricket team, the Victoria Pearls, will face off against their counterparts from Nepal and the USA in the inaugural Easter Women’s T20 Cup, set to begin on 7th April at Entebbe Cricket Oval. The nine-day tournament brings together a mix of emerging international sides and local talent as a build-up ahead of the Emerging Tournament and the Kwibuka Cup.

